<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002040/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Continous evaluation (class attendance is mandatory)
Grading:
40% exam (points awarded should be > 4) on the day specified in the final exam schedule
30% individual assignments (to be solved in the classroom)
30% group project (3-4 students)
On the day of the exam, each group will make an oral presentation and will submit:
Presentation
OpenMC inputs (with proper use of commenting to ease understanding)
The presentation will include:
Objectives: why the study carried out is of interest, what is intended to be calculated and for what
Modeling with OpenMC (difficulties encountered, way to solve them, hypotheses made, . . . )
Simulations carried out and discussion of the obtained results
Conclusions
Consulted bibliography
Grading will be based on the technical content of the presentation and demonstrated acquisition of knowledge; didactics for transmission of knowledge.

Final examination
Grading:
40% theoretical exam
60% by solving a practical problem using a Monte Carlo code"""@es ;
